A truck carrying explosives for a gold mine crashed with a motorbike in Ghana on Thursday triggering an explosion that left hundreds of buildings damaged and several people dead, officials have said. President Nana Akufo-Addo has called it a "tragic incident."           The incident happened around noon in the west of the country, near the city of Bogoso, about 300 km (180 miles) west of the capital, Accra. Police said a preliminary investigation has established and most of the victims have been rescued and taken to nearby hospitals. They also urged the public "to remain calm." The truck involved in the crash and explosion was en route to the Chirano gold mine.